description: From Latin concameratus, past participle of concamero (“to arch over”), from con- + camera (“chamber, vault”). See camber.

verbs.description: concamerate (third-person singular simple present concamerates, present participle concamerating, simple past and past participle concamerated)

entries.meaning: To divide into chambers or cells.
examples: Of those which have the top formed into a kind of rostrum and crooked , and are not concamerated within
